<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Book Typography" href="Book_Typography">book typography</a> and production, a <a title="Recto" href="Recto">recto</a> page on which is printed the title of the book and which falls between the <a title="Front Matter" href="Front_Matter">front matter</a> and the first page of the main text of the book. A half-title page also falls as the very first page of the book, preceding the <a title="Title Page" href="Title_Page">title page</a>, and in this case is also known as a <a title="Bastard Title" href="Bastard_Title">bastard title</a> or <a title="False Title" href="False_Title">false title</a>. 
</p>
